{"word":"ὀβελίσκος","slug":"ὀβελίσκος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ὀβελίσκος</b></el> <el>(ὀβελίσκος, ὁ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:Diminutive'>Dim.</a> of <a href='S:ὀβελός'><el>ὀβελός</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a small spit</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>a coin stamped with a spit</i>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>the leg of a compass</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}